<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[810,1452,1274,1589]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,932,1274,1300]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The group 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1177,1274,1300]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tarsalis">
<emphasis box="[1093,1177,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">tarsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the following combination of characters: medium total length; legs and palps without coloration patterns; bulb with three keels; serrated area distal to PAc in prolateral view of copulatory bulb absent or small; BTA absent; embolus inserted in a right angle; embolar apex flattened and expanded, arrow-shaped in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[810,1452,1274,1589]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
